Sri Venkateswara Medical College is a medical college in Tirupati, Andhra Pradesh, India, established in 1960. It has 240 undergraduate and 146 postgraduate seats. The college is recognised by National Medical Council.
Teaching hospitals
*SRi Venkateswara Ramnarain Ruia Government General Hospital (SVRRGGH)
Govt Maternity Hospital & Institute of Pregnant Women
